<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD INSPECTION - PRESSURE
        CHECK CYLINDER HEAD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="4">
        <title>PRESSURE CHECK CYLINDER HEAD</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressure testing the cylinder head will reveal cracks in ports or nozzle sleeve leakage
                which cannot be observed using dye penetrant. Pressure-test the cylinder head as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Reinstall injection nozzles before pressure testing.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Nozzle clamping seals the nozzle sleeve at the bottom of the bore in the cylinder head.
                            Good nozzle sleeves will be condemned needlessly if nozzles are not installed prior to
                            pressure testing.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef4150419" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12031" filename="../figcg1/cg12031.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.19. Example of Cylinder Head Crack.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150420" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12032" filename="../figcg1/cg12032.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.20. Mineral Spirits Test for Valve Leakage.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150421" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12033" filename="../figcg1/cg12033.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.21. Inspect Valves for Leakage.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the valves, using a valve spring compressor. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150403.xml" xrefid="hl4150403">"CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING"</hotlnk>, in
                    this section for valve removal instructions.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Pressure test cylinder head using Cylinder Head Pressure Testing Kit SE-4289 (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150422">4.22</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150422" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14648" filename="../figcg1/cg14648.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.22. Cylinder Head Pressure Testing Kit SE-4289.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fasten the pressure plate and head gasket to the cylinder head gasket surface using the
                    mounting bolts and nuts supplied with the kit. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150403.xml" xrefid="ef4150423">4.23</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Fasten the block-off plate and thermostat housing gasket to the thermostat opening.
                    Remove the pipe plug next to the thermostat opening. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150403.xml" xrefid="ef4150424">4.24</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install a hose fitting to the cylinder head at the removed plug. Attach a "hot" water
                    source to the fitting and fill the cylinder head with water. Apply 124-138 kPa (18-20 psi) water
                    pressure and visually inspect for leaks at the:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Nozzle sleeves</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Ports</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Upper deck</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Lower deck</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If leakage is observed at any port or the upper and lower deck, REPLACE THE CYLINDER HEAD.
                            If nozzle sleeve leakage is observed, follow the procedures under
                            <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150403.xml" xrefid="hl4150403">"CYLINDER HEAD
                                RECONDITIONING"</hotlnk>.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
